### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  api-tests.http  –  Tests REST API & GraphQL
###  Extension VSCode requise : REST Client (humao.rest-client)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@adminUser = admin
@adminPass = Admin@Secure2024!

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. WP REST API v2 – Récupérer les articles
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### GET Articles
GET {{baseUrl}}/wp-json/wp/v2/posts?per_page=5
Accept: application/json

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. WP REST API v2 – Récupérer les pages
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### GET Pages
GET {{baseUrl}}/wp-json/wp/v2/pages
Accept: application/json

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. WP REST API v2 – Obtenir un JWT token
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### POST /wp-json/jwt-auth/v1/token
POST {{baseUrl}}/wp-json/jwt-auth/v1/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{adminUser}}",
  "password": "{{adminPass}}"
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. WP REST API v2 – Créer un article (authentifié)
#    Remplacer <JWT_TOKEN> par le token obtenu ci-dessus
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### POST Article (nécessite JWT)
@jwtToken = <JWT_TOKEN>

POST {{baseUrl}}/wp-json/wp/v2/posts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

{
  "title": "Article de test via REST API",
  "content": "Contenu créé par l'API REST WordPress.",
  "status": "publish"
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. WPGraphQL – Introspection
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### GraphQL Introspection
POST {{baseUrl}}/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ __schema { types { name } } }"
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. WPGraphQL – Query articles
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### GraphQL – Posts
POST {{baseUrl}}/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ posts(first: 5) { nodes { id title date excerpt } } }"
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. WPGraphQL – Query pages
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
### GraphQL – Pages
POST {{baseUrl}}/graphql
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "{ pages { nodes { id title uri content } } }"
}

###
